10000.Name: Aru
10000.ProfileIntroduction:
The self-proclaimed boss of Problem Solver 68.

Aru expanded the Gehenna Academy's Problem Solver 68 club without permission to conduct illegal business activities. She aspires to be seen as a dashing and debonair villain, but her frequent blunders always expose her as a poser.

Skills.Desc: Fires a shot that deals <?1> damage to one enemy and explodes for an additional <?2> damage to enemies in a circular area around the target.

Skills.Name: Noir Attack
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, fires a shot that deals <?1> damage to one enemy with a 50% chance to explode for an additional <?2> damage to enemies in a circular area around the target.

Skills.Name: Noir Attack+
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, fires a shot that deals <?1> damage to one enemy with a 100% chance to explode for an additional <?2> damage to enemies in a circular area around the target.

Skills.Name: The Gravity of a Boss
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: The Gravity of a Boss+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Way of the Outlaw
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> for the duration of Aru's EX skill.

Weapon.Name: Wine Red/Admire
Weapon.Desc:
A semi-automatic sniper rifle with an antique design cherished by Aru.

Her hard-boiled nature intensifies just by carrying it.

Gear.Name: Aru's Very Precious Wallet
Gear.Desc: A high-quality wallet Aru loves. Although it's made of fine material, it's faded and scratched due to long use. Haruka, Kayoko, and Mutsuki saved up and gave it to Aru as a gift after Problem Solver 68 was first established, so it's irreplaceable to her.

10001.Name: Eimi
10001.CharacterSSRNew: How can I fight more effectively?
10001.ProfileIntroduction:
An agent of the Super Phenomenon Task Force at the Millennium School.

An emotionally inscrutable oddball, Eimi very rarely speaks and can often be found staring off into space for no particular reason. However, there's no one as brutally efficient as her when it comes to carrying out missions for Seminar.

Skills.Desc: Gains <b:DotHeal>, continuously restoring 3.4% of Eimi's lost HP plus <?1> of Healing every 1s for 20s.

Skills.Desc: Every 15s, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area.

Skills.Name: Single-Minded Assault+
Skills.Desc: Every 15s, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area and restores own HP by <?2> of Healing.

Skills.Name: Specialist's Respite
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealEffectiveness> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Specialist's Respite+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealEffectiveness> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Iron Will
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:OppressionResist> by <?1> while Eimi's HP is below 50%.

Weapon.Name: Multi Tactical
Weapon.Desc:
Eimi's favorite shotgun with a crude design.

Multifaceted like its name suggests, used on everything from forced breakthroughs to dealing with supernatural phenomena.

10002.Name: Haruna
10002.CharacterSSRNew: Shall we explore the world of fine dining?
10002.ProfileIntroduction:
President of the Gehenna Gourmet Research Society.

At a glance, she appears to possess the graceful charisma of a refined lady. But when it comes to food, she can turn into a deranged maniac at the flip of a switch. Despite her uncontrollable gluttony, she actually can't stomach too much food at once. Her favorite foods are those rich in fat, such as motsunabe and horumonyaki.

Skills.Name: Piercing Elegance
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in a straight line. Damage to subsequent enemies is reduced by 10% per enemy hit (to a minimum of 30% damage).

Skills.Name: Exotic Explosives
Skills.Desc: Every 30s, deals <?1> damage to one enemy.

Skills.Name: Gourmand's Honor
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Gourmand's Honor+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Prudent Connoisseur
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> while Haruna is standing still.

Weapon.Name: Ideal
Weapon.Desc:
An elegant sniper rifle used by Haruna.

She claims she can see the path to becoming the ultimate gourmand through the scope.

10003.Name: Hifumi
10003.CharacterSSRNew: If Sensei's going to be with me...I'm going to give my all!
10003.ProfileIntroduction:
A friendly, outgoing member of the Trinity Make-Up Work Club.

Hifumi's just a regular girl with average grades, but she's nonetheless well liked and popular for her well-rounded personality. She's a good listener for anyone who needs to vent about their worries or problems, but this also causes her to get swept up in the moment and unintentionally cause trouble.
10003.Hobby: Collecting Peroro merch, shopping, listening to others

Skills.Name: Help Me, Peroro!
Skills.Desc: Summons a Peroro plush with 160% of Hifumi's <b:MAXHP>, dealing <?1> damage to enemies in a circular area and inflicting <c:Provoke> for <?2>.

Skills.Name: Peroro's Support
Skills.Desc: Every 35s, deals 212% damage to one enemy and decrease their <d:HIT> by <?1> for 30s.

Skills.Name: Collector's Spirit
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Collector's Spirit+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Agile Collector
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CostRegen> by <?1> for 5s after Hifumi uses her EX skill.

Weapon.Name: My Necessity
Weapon.Desc:
A pink rifle carried around by Hifumi.

Hifumi doesn't go anywhere without this cute pink-painted rifle.

10004.Name: Hina
10004.CharacterSSRNew:
It's annoying, but I should take care of it.
That's my job.
10004.ProfileIntroduction:
Head prefect of the Gehenna Academy Prefect Team.

Somewhat aloof and considers almost everything a bother and a chore, but is still every bit the head prefect of the Prefect Team when it comes to rules and regulations.
Her general response to most things is "Ugh, so annoying," but she's ruthless and decisive when it comes to matters on the battlefield.
Feared and respected by the enemies of Gehenna.

Skills.Name: Denouement: Ishbosheth
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area.

Skills.Name: Lock & Load
Skills.Desc: Whenever Hina runs out of ammo, immediately reloads and increases <b:ATK> by <?1> for 16s.

Skills.Name: Prefect Team Member Judgment
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Prefect Team Member Judgment+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> and <b:AttackSpeed> by <?2>.

Skills.Name: Out-and-Out
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage as an additional hit to enemies not taking cover.

Weapon.Name: Destroyer of Denouement
Weapon.Desc:
A multipurpose machine gun Hina wields as naturally as any limb.

Blows away school rule violators and degenerates with its ruthlessly destructive power.

10005.Name: Hoshino
10005.CharacterSSRNew:
It's way past my nap time,
but I'll help if you want me to.
10005.ProfileIntroduction:
The Abydos Student Council vice president and president of the Foreclosure Task Force.

Acts more like a tired old timer and would rather play pranks than do actual work. This often gets her into trouble with her fellow task force members, but once on a mission, she fights harder on the front lines than anyone else to keep her friends safe.

Skills.Name: Tactical Suppression
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area.<?2>

Skills.Name: Emergency First Aid
Skills.Desc: Once per battle when HP falls below 30%, gains <b:DotHeal>, continuously restoring HP equal to <?1> of Healing every 4s for 20s.

Skills.Name: Foreclosure Task Force President
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:DEF> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Foreclosure Task Force President+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:DEF> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Expert Suppression
Skills.Desc: Whenever Hoshino uses her EX skill, gains a <b:Shield> with HP equal to <?1> of Healing. Barrier is dispelled once EX skill has finished.

Weapon.Name: Eye of Horus
Weapon.Desc:
Hoshino's favorite shotgun with a simple design.

The normally lazy Hoshino never slacks when it comes to weapon maintenance.

10006.Name: Iori
10006.ProfileIntroduction:
A cold-blooded specialist of Gehenna Academy's Prefect Team.

She uses her overwhelming force as field captain to ruthlessly discipline offenders. Iori is highly efficient and formidable in combat, but her stubbornness causes her to fall for even the most obvious traps.

Skills.Name: Major Roundup
Skills.Desc: Fires 3 shots at an enemy that each deal <?1> damage to the target and enemies in a fan-shaped area behind them.

Skills.Name: Bounty
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, deals <?1> damage to one enemy.

Skills.Name: One-Shot Bullseye
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HIT> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: One-Shot Bullseye+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HIT> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Prefect Team Nerve
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage as an additional hit to enemies if Iori is not taking cover.

Weapon.Name: Crack Shot
Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle used by Iori to deal with fugitives.

A bare-bones sniper rifle that lacks even a scope because, Iori says, a specialist never blames their tools.

10007.Name: Maki
10007.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of Veritas, a hacker group at the Millennium Science School.

A mischievous student who enjoys drawing graffiti and designed Veritas' emblem. She has a flighty personality and doesn't take anything seriously, which often sparks conflict with other clubs.

Skills.Name: World Beautification!
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to one enemy and increases <b:ATK> by <?2> for 30s.

Skills.Name: Paintball Lob!
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, marks one enemy and decreases their <d:DEF> by <?1> for 15s.

Skills.Name: Dazzling Display
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Dazzling Display+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Suffering for Art
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage as an additional hit to enemies marked by Maki.

Weapon.Name: Auto Lacquer
Weapon.Desc:
Maki's multipurpose machine gun often used when drawing graffiti.

Modified using Millennium's technology, it can load and fire paintballs along with live ammunition.

10008.Name: Neru
10008.CharacterSSRNew: Shout! Give it everything you've got!
10008.ProfileIntroduction:
President of C&C, a secret organization of the Millennium School.

At first glance, Neru looks like nothing but a young delinquent with a flashy bomber jacket draped over her maid outfit, but in reality she's Millennium's most formidable agent. Within Millennium, her call sign, Double O, is seen as a sign of certain victory.

Skills.Name: You Got a Death Wish or Somethin'?
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to one enemy. Damage increases by <?2> times if Neru is <s:Fury>.

Skills.Name: Cruisin' for a Bruisin'!
Skills.Desc: Every 30s, Neru becomes <s:Fury> and her <b:Dodge> increases by <?1> for 20s.

Skills.Name: Cruisin' for a Bruisin'!+
Skills.Desc: Every 30s, Neru becomes and her increases by for 20s. Improves the increase to EX Skill damage by an additional 0.3× while .

Skills.Name: Codename Double O
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Codename Double O+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Enhanced Rage
Skills.Desc: Whenever Neru becomes <s:Fury>, increases <b:ATK> by <?1> for 30s.

Weapon.Name: Twin Dragons
Weapon.Desc:
A pair of SMGs used by Neru.

Both are lavishly engraved with a golden dragon pattern.

Gear.Name: Neru's Bomber Jacket
Gear.Desc: A bomber jacket that Neru doesn't want to separate from for a single moment. If you ask her about it, she has a very simple answer for you...

10009.Name: Izumi
10009.CharacterSSRNew: The world is full of delicious food!
10009.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Gehenna Gourmet Research Society with a voracious appetite.

She loves food so much that she even gobbles up dishes that others would dislike with gusto.

Skills.Name: Cheese 'n' Chocolate Hamburger!
Skills.Desc: Restores own HP by <?1> of Healing<?2>.

Skills.Name: Ready, Set, Boom!
Skills.Desc: Whenever Izumi uses normal attacks, she has a 20% chance to deal <?1> damage to one enemy. 10s cooldown between activations.

Skills.Name: Ready, Set, Boom!+
Skills.Desc: Whenever Izumi uses normal attacks, she has a 20% chance to deal <?1> damage to one enemy. 10s cooldown between activations.

Skills.Name: What to Eat Next?
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealEffectiveness> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: What to Eat Next?+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealEffectiveness> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Savor the Flavor!
Skills.Desc: Deals between <?1> ~ <?2> damage as an additional hit to enemies based on Izumi's current HP.

Weapon.Name: Daily Cutlery
Weapon.Desc:
A heavy machine gun used by Izumi.

The more troublemakers the gun defeats, the more delicious her food becomes.

10010.Name: Shiroko
10010.ProfileIntroduction:
The sporty field captain of the Abydos Foreclosure Task Force.

A girl of few words and almost no facial expression, Shiroko gives the impression of being frigid and emotionless. In truth, she is more devoted to the Abydos High School than anything else. If it's for the sake of revitalizing the academy, she'll do whatever it takes and sometimes propose some outlandish ideas herself.

Skills.Name: Drone Support
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to one enemy.

Skills.Name: Grenade Lob
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a circular area.

Skills.Name: Grenade Lob+
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a circular area.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Target Weaknesses+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Very Rapid Fire
Skills.Desc: Normal attacks have a 20% chance to increase <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1> for 30s. 25s cooldown between activations.

Weapon.Name: White Fang 465
Weapon.Desc:
Shiroko's favorite assault rifle.

Always ready to be used in any situation due to diligent maintenance.

Gear.Name: Shiroko's Drone
Gear.Desc: A drone that Shiroko always has on standby. She claims it is for filming herself exercising, but there are many upgrades attached that seem to serve other purposes.

10011.Name: Shun
10011.CharacterSSRNew: Have you been waiting patiently for me? My, you're such a good kid.
10011.ProfileIntroduction:
Instructor of Shanhaijing's Disciplinary Support Department, Plum Blossom Garden.

An instructor to young students at the Plum Blossom Garden. The little students hold her and Shanhaijing in high regard. She is seldom angered by the mischievous antics of her young students due to her extensive experience. However, asking her age is off limits.

Skills.Name: Where Did You Go, You Rascals?
Skills.Desc: Augments <s:FormChange> to deal 153% damage and prioritise the enemy with the highest ATK, increases <b:Range> by 24.2% and <b:CriticalChance> by <?1>, but decreases <d:AttackSpeed> by 18.8% for 30s.

Skills.Name: Pay Attention, Everyone!
Skills.Desc: Generates <?1> units of skill cost once at the start of battle.

Skills.Name: Instructor's Poise
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Instructor's Poise+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Plum Blossom Training
Skills.Desc: Deals damage as an additional hit to medium sized enemies.

Weapon.Name: Halcon de Amor
Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle inlaid with Shun's favorite pattern.

Any naughty child becomes obedient in front of Shun's Tough Love.

10012.Name: Sumire
10012.ProfileIntroduction:
Leader of the Millennium Athletic Training Club.

An athletic girl with a passion for physical training. She is very much a jock and believes all problems can be solved with muscles and exercise.

Skills.Name: Shoot and Score
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area.

Skills.Name: Warm-Up
Skills.Desc: Every 40s, increases <b:ATK> by <?1> for 20s.

Skills.Name: Pinpoint Attack
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Pinpoint Attack+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MAXHP> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Tension Boost!
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:DEF> by <?1> while not inflicted with a Crowd Control effect.

Weapon.Name: Modern Millennium Dumbbell
Weapon.Desc:
A semi-automatic shotgun that Sumire uses regularly when exercising.

Can improve one's health by doing a push-up with each shot fired.

10013.Name: Tsurugi
10013.ProfileIntroduction:
President of Trinity's Justice Task Force and its official strategic weapon.

She is belligerent and violent, with a tendency to destroy anything she doesn't like. However, thanks to the painstaking efforts of the task force's vice president, Hasumi, the club has managed to hold itself together. Tsurugi is like a beast that can't be controlled, but even she can't help but soften up when she's with her Sensei.

Skills.Name: Bizarre Devastation
Skills.Desc: Immediately reloads, augments <s:FormChange> to deal 138% damage to enemies in a fan-shaped area and increases <b:ATK> by <?1>. Effect ends after Tsurugi reloads <?2>. (Normal Attack changes to hit 2 times)

Skills.Name: Intense Passion
Skills.Desc: Whenever Tsurugi defeats an enemy, restores own HP by <?1> of Healing. 10s cooldown between activations.

Skills.Name: Intense Passion+
Skills.Desc: Whenever Tsurugi defeats an enemy, restores own HP by <?1> of Healing and increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?2> for 20s. 10s cooldown between activations.

Skills.Name: Agility
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:MoveSpeed> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Agility+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:AmmoCount> by <?1> and <b:MoveSpeed> by <?2>.

Skills.Name: Uncontrollable Power
Skills.Desc: Whenever Tsurugi defeats an enemy, she has a <?1> chance to restore 1 ammo to her weapon.

Weapon.Name: Blood 'n' Gunpowder
Weapon.Desc:
Twin shotguns used by Tsurugi.

One is named "Blood" and the other is named "Gunpowder."
Both are equally terrifying, with no particular distinction between them.

Gear.Name: Tsurugi's Special Chest
Gear.Desc: A box full of goods hiding deep inside Tsurugi's room. Various, random things are piled up in it: collectibles, books, movie tickets, and more. You can get a glimpse of Tsurugi's meticulousness just by looking at how neatly everything's organized, without a single speck of dust.

10014.Name: Izuna
10014.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Hyakkiyako Academy's Ninjutsu Research Club.

A bright and bubbly young girl, but her devotion to her strange dream has caused her to spend most of her life as a loner. She devotes herself to becoming the best ninja she can every day. That also includes following around and referring to Sensei as her lord among other things.
10014.Hobby: Studying the art of ninjutsu, squiring her lord

Skills.Name: Izuna Ninja Scrolls!
Skills.Desc: Repositions to the selected location and increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1> for 30s.

Skills.Name: Secret Weapon, Exploding Shurikens!
Skills.Desc: Every 6 normal attacks, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a circular area.

Skills.Name: Izuna-Style Prickly Ninjutsu!
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Izuna-Style Prickly Ninjutsu!+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Izuna-Style Rapid Growth Ninjutsu!
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> for 30s after Izuna uses her EX skill.

Weapon.Name: Izuna-Style Super Ninja Tool
Weapon.Desc:
Izuna's favorite submachine gun.

A cutting-edge ninja tool used in conjunction with Izuna-Style Ninjutsu. Can fire smoke bombs and even massage her lord's shoulders. Its uses are endless.

10015.Name: Aris
10015.CharacterSSRNew: I've been waiting for your call for a long time.
10015.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Game Development Department at the Millennium School.

A mysterious girl who was found sleeping within some ruins. All information regarding Aris' age and origins is unknown. Currently, she has become a hardcore video game fanatic thanks to Midori and Momoi. The majority of her inarticulate speech is comprised of dialog from retro video games.

Skills.Name: Balance Breakdown
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in a straight line. Damage increases by 1.5 or 2 times depending on current <s:EnergyBatteryHalf> level (resets after use).

Skills.Name: Bright Light!
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> for 20s and increases <s:EnergyBatteryHalf> level by one (maximum level is 2).

Skills.Name: Enhanced Magic!
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Enhanced Magic!+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Supernova Awakening!
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> for 20s when Aris uses her EX skill. Effect increases by 1.5 or 2 times depending on <s:EnergyBatteryHalf> level.

Weapon.Name: Supernova: The Sword of Light
Weapon.Desc:
A massive railgun Aris received from the Engineering Department.

Its weight and power output are so great that ordinary students would have trouble just carrying it.

10016.Name: Midori
10016.CharacterSSRNew: I'm very proud of how this illustration turned out!
10016.ProfileIntroduction:
Illustrator of the Game Development Department at the Millennium School.

Both Midori and her twin sister, Momoi, develop games with the Game Development Department.
Though her introverted personality had previously put her at odds with her more gregarious older sister, the two are now inseparable thanks to their shared love of video games.

Skills.Name: Drawing Art
Skills.Desc: Fires 5 shots that target up to 5 different enemies, each shot dealing <?1> damage. If Momoi is in the same unit, each shot deals an additional <?2> <d:Poison> damage every 4s for 20s.

Skills.Name: Artistic Polish
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, restores the HP of the ally with the lowest HP (except herself) for <?1> of Healing.

Skills.Name: Artist's Inspiration
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Artist's Inspiration+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Developmental Synergy: Momoi
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:AttackSpeed> by <?1>. If Momoi is in the same unit, increases by <?2> instead.

Weapon.Name: Fresh Inspiration
Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle used by Midori.

Fitted with an accessory from her big sister, which Midori fidgets with in a pinch. It always seems to spark an idea.

10017.Name: Cherino
10017.CharacterSSRNew: Feel the glory of facing me!
10017.ProfileIntroduction:
Student council president of Red Winter Academy.

Greedy and obsessed with power, she loses her position in a revolution once a week but somehow always regains her authority. Cherino believes her power comes from the fake mustache she wears as a symbol of authority.

The leader of the RABBIT Squad at the SRT Academy. Her call sign is "RABBIT 1."

10044.Name: Nonomi (Swimsuit)

10044.ProfileIntroduction:

10046.Name: Izuna (Swimsuit)
10046.CharacterSSRNew: This summer I'm gonna train hard with my lord!
10046.ProfileIntroduction: A member of the Hyakkiyako Academy Ninjutsu Research Club who went to the beach for summer training. She's a ninja who's always very lively. 10047.Name: Chise (Swimsuit)
10047.CharacterSSRNew: The ocean is full of interesting things!
10047.ProfileIntroduction: An airhead who's a member of the Yin-Yang Club. She likes to hang out in the sunlight. Chise is spending a fulfilling summer with Sensei, looking for sparkles and poking turtles.

Secretary for the Millennium School Student Council, Seminar.

Her main responsibility is to maintain Seminar's official records, but she also handles various other legal and administrative duties, such as overseeing patent applications and product evaluations for Millennium student creations. Her extraordinary memory allows her 
to almost perfectly remember anything she's read or heard once.

10053.Name: Yuuka (Track)
10053.CharacterSSRNew: Perfectly prepared for this year's Kivotos Halo Festival!
10053.ProfileIntroduction:
The Seminar treasurer, changed into gym clothes to participate in the Kivotos Halo Festival.

Despite having already suffered from a heavy workload preparing for the big event, all she needed was a good night's rest to be back in tip-top condition. As a member of Seminar, Yuuka wants to focus on being a calm, rational representative of the council and ambassador to Kivotos, but the competitiveness of her fellow students is more infectious than she would ever admit.

10054.Name: Mari (Track)
10054.CharacterSSRNew: May we enter this field day as competitors and leave as friends...
10054.ProfileIntroduction:
A student from the Sisterhood. She's dressed in track clothes to participate in the Kivotos Halo Festival.

She eagerly volunteered for the Executive Committee, believing deeply in the festival's purpose: wishing for peace in Kivotos. However, the festival has been mired in trouble and conflict, and, due to her dedication, Mari has been caught up by it too.

A pistol carried by Mari.

It's usually used for peaceful purposes, such as to signal the start of a match. However, at times Mari finds it inadvertently pointed towards troublemaking students.

10055.Name: Shigure
10055.CharacterSSRNew: Do you need a place to warm up? Heehee... Just let me know.
10055.ProfileIntroduction:
A student suspended from Red Winter Academy and on probation in Former Institute 227.

She was suspended for mixing alcohol into the school-issued kompot. She's an old friend of Nodoka from Spec Ops No. 227. The rumor is that she caused trouble on purpose after Nodoka was sent to Former Institute 227 as punishment in order to join her friend. Whether or not this is true, she loves homemade kompot and always carries a flask in her pocket.

A multi-grenade launcher that Shigure is never without.

Anyone hit by the grenades will be knocked senseless.

10056.Name: Serina (Christmas)
10056.CharacterSSRNew: The Remedial Knights are here to deliver Christmas cheer! Merry Christmas to all!
10056.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Trinity Remedial Knights. She's dressed in a Santa outfit to celebrate Christmas.

She's spending her Christmas volunteering for charity work. Anyone who watches her singing carols and giving out her handmade gifts would think that she was an angel who came down from heaven for Christmas.

It doesn't fire needles, but it carries a double dose of Serina's love.

10057.Name: Haruna (New Year)
10057.CharacterSSRNew: What's more appetizing than seasonal food? For the New Year, we could have osechi, ozoni, oshiruko... Oh, now I'm hungry.
10057.ProfileIntroduction:
The president of the Gourmet Research Society, who got dressed up in a kimono for the New Year.

She believes all aspects of a situation are crucial for a gourmand: not just the time and place of the meal, but also wearing the appropriate outfit. Therefore, she has set out on the path of epicureanism wearing a kimono. She certainly seems elegant and refined, but...if she's served food that doesn't meet her standards, watch out.

Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle used by Haruna.

She will have no partner more suitable than this gun as she continues the path of a true gourmand.

10058.Name: Mine
10058.CharacterSSRNew: I'm Aomori Mine, Remedial Knights captain. Does anyone need medical assistance?
10058.ProfileIntroduction:
The captain of the Trinity Remedial Knights. A true knight in shining armor, she's upright and resolute, but she has a radical side as well.

She has a reputation in Trinity: Mine destroys things, and her knights pick up the pieces. She spends her spare time maintaining her equipment and making snacks and drinks for get-togethers with her friends. Some say that she knows as much about black tea as Hasumi of the Justice Task Force.

Mine's shotgun.

She always says that there are two sides to a cure.
Is this weapon one of them?

10059.CharacterSSRNew: Thanks for waiting! It's my turn to jump in! ‚òÜ
10059.ProfileIntroduction:
The former leader of Pater, one of the allied factions that makes up Trinity General School.

A former Tea Party member and a childhood friend of Nagisa, another member of the Tea Party. When the two clash politically, she draws a clear line between their public disagreements and their private friendship.
She seems lively and cheerful, and she's never without a smile. However, her demeanor hides worries that she can't reveal, making her something of an enigma.

Mika's favorite submachine gun.

It was originally an ordinary Trinity-made submachine gun before Mika decorated it with love. Now, it shines like a star in the dark sky. You can be sure it's had a role in everything Mika does.

10060.Name: Megu
10060.CharacterSSRNew: Is there a problem? Let me handle it!
10060.ProfileIntroduction:
The backbone of the Hot Springs Department and foreman at their construction sites.

She believes with all her heart that demolition can solve any problem.
Her personality is bold and confident, and she's earned the trust of everyone in the Hot Springs Department due to her excellent demolition skills.

Megu's one-of-a-kind flamethrower. When she takes it out, it becomes like an extension of her.

No one else can handle it due to the immense amounts of heat it gives off. Its interesting name comes from a pun that someone made about her once.

10061.Name: Sakurako
10061.CharacterSSRNew: Through every trial you face, I'll watch over you.
10061.ProfileIntroduction:
The faithful head student of Trinity's Sisterhood.

Her sincerity shines through all her actions, making her trusted by many.
She'll take up any duty given to her with piety and serenity. However, when it comes to matters of fashion or everyday life, her traditional nature sometimes causes her trouble.

A gun that's maintained with all the thoroughness and reverence that Sakurako possesses.

Others find it difficult to even touch.

10062.Name: Toki
10062.CharacterSSRNew: Leave it to me. I'm both the perfect agent and the perfect maid.
10062.ProfileIntroduction:
The mysterious fifth agent of Millennium Academy's secret spy agency, C&C.

Although she technically belongs to C&C, she's been Rio's exclusive maid and bodyguard for some time, so few know who Toki is. While she is a superior secret agent who's at ease with high-tech weaponry and technology, she seems to be a bit lonely as she always works solo.

Weapon.Desc:
Toki's one-of-a-kind assault rifle.

With performance as exceptional as its appearance suggests, it can crush any obstacle and complete any mission. She didn't name it herself, but it's unknown who did.

10063.Name: Koyuki
10063.CharacterSSRNew: When the plan falls apart, well... That's when life gets interesting!
10063.ProfileIntroduction:
A brilliant yet troublesome member of Millennium's Seminar.

She's completely unaware of her unrivaled talent for mathematical decryption. She always sets out to test her luck. Even if she goes too far and lands in hot water, she never stops.

Serika nags a lot and does not hesitate to let her opinions be known. Despite her habit of bashing the academy, saying, "To hell with this academy!" she is secretly quite devoted to it and even works part-time jobs to try and help pay off the academy's debts.

13011.Name: Momoi
13011.ProfileIntroduction:
Scenario writer of the Game Development Department at the Millennium School.

Both Momoi and her twin sister, Midori, develop games with the Game Development Department. Though her lighthearted and cheerful personality previously put her at odds with her more introverted little sister, the two are now inseparable thanks to their shared love of video games.

13012.Name: Kirino
13012.ProfileIntroduction:
A passionate cadet of the Valkyrie Police School's Public Safety Bureau.

She enrolled in the Valkyrie Police School because of her admiration for the upperclassmen, but was transferred to the Public Safety Bureau due to her poor marksmanship. However, she still works hard and dreams of becoming an officer who can gloriously subdue criminals.

16000.Name: Haruka
16000.ProfileIntroduction:
A senior member of Problem Solver 68.

Her gloomy personality has made her the target of bullies since childhood. Only recently was Aru able to help her put a stop to the harassment. Since then, she has been the youngest senior member of Problem Solver 68. She may be timid and have painfully low self-esteem, but may also be the most terrifying member of her club because of her ideas alone.

Or uses to exterminate "pest-like things".

16001.Name: Asuna
16001.ProfileIntroduction:
An agent of C&C, a secret organization of the Millennium School.

Armed with brutal instinct and intuition, Asuna is a seasoned veteran who has successfully overcome countless challenges under the call sign Zero-One. She is also something of a loose cannon, doing things such as revealing her identity on secret missions and smashing anything that looks suspicious without a second thought. However, she always manages to produce great results in the end.

16002.Name: Kotori
16002.ProfileIntroduction:
Member of the Engineering Department at the Millennium Science School.

A chatterbox who loves discussing topics such as physics and mechanics. She's always the first one at the scene to explain what's happening whenever there's a machinery-related problem at Millennium.

When asked about its name, Kotori begins by talking about the history of firearm development.

16003.Name: Suzumi
16003.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Vigilante Crew responsible for protecting Trinity's students.

To combat the increasing number of attacks on Trinity's students at the hands of the other academies, Suzumi volunteered to patrol the streets to abate attackers. Often misunderstood as cold and unfeeling due to her strong sense of justice, she actually has a friendly side as well.

A precious companion for Suzumi, who always patrols the neighborhood alone.

Gear.Desc: The headphones Suzumi carries on patrol. Calling them "Patrol Headphones" is a bit self-indulgent as they are a relatively common product.

16004.Name: Pina
16004.ProfileIntroduction:
A devout vigilante admirer attending Hyakkiyako Academy.

Pina has a bubbly, energetic personality and takes pleasure in helping others. Everything she knows about vigilantes comes from movies, so the accuracy of said knowledge can be somewhat dubious. Nonetheless, she persists in her ambition of becoming a vigilante herself.

Weapon.Name: Indiscriminate Shooter
Weapon.Desc:
Pina's stationary machine gun.

The non-stop heat it emits is as fiery as Pina's own heart.

16005.Name: Tsurugi (Swimsuit)
16005.ProfileIntroduction:
Trinity's Justice Task Force's president comes to the beach in pursuit of the romance of youth.

She tries her best to suppress her violent temperament famous for being Trinity's greatest weapon and enjoy her youth on vacation...but the beach didn't pan out the way she wanted.

Weapon.Name: Blood 'n' Gunpowder
Weapon.Desc:
Two shotguns used by Tsurugi.

Can still fire without issue even after being submerged underwater.

16006.Name: Izumi (Swimsuit)
16006.ProfileIntroduction:
A Gehenna Gourmet Research Society member with a gluttonous appetite even during the summer.

She visits the beach with a watermelon in one hand and an ice cooler in the other in search of renown summer delicacies: Chocolate-flavored grilled unagi, spicy shaved ice, watermelon sprinkled with mint chocolate, and more. Her pursuit of various delicacies in Kivotos are second to none as her peculiar excursions continue even on the hot summer beach.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:Stability> by <?1> and <b:AttackSpeed> by <?2>.

Weapon.Desc:
A heavy machine gun used by Izumi.

Even now, Izumi's gun burns in search of a gourmet summer experience! It's even complete with waterproof functionality!

16007.Name: Tomoe
16007.ProfileIntroduction:
The chief secretary of the Red Winter Office and President Cherino's closest aide.

A speaking master who can wrap up and deliver just about any message. She gives regular speeches at the academy to inspire loyalty to President Cherino. Cherino believes Tomoe is loyal because she is smitten by her charisma, but in fact, Tomoe simply finds Cherino adorable.

A long sniper rifle used by Tomoe.

Equipped with a high-res telescopic sight making it possible to spot targets from afar and dispose of any insubordinate who doubts the authority of President Cherino.

16008.Name: Fubuki
16008.ProfileIntroduction:
A laid-back administrative advisor of the Valkyrie Police School.

She entered Valkyrie longing for a laid-back, easygoing life as a civil servant. She remains negligent, enjoying life as it is without being swayed by money or fame even when a case is sent to the Public Safety Bureau. Her favorite activity is eating donuts while listening to the radio.

Weapon.Desc:
A standard rifle that Fubuki received from the Valkyrie Police School.

It's pretty powerful, but it doesn't function properly because Fubuki has neglected to take care of it.

16009.Name: Michiru
16009.ProfileIntroduction:
The president of the Hyakkiyako Academy Ninjutsu Research Club and admin of the video channel Michiruchi, a Girl's Ninja Scroll.

Michiru tends to operate from a place of complete, unfounded confidence. As a ninja otaku, she works tirelessly with the other members to make ninjas popular throughout Kivotos. Her dreams are to make the Ninjutsu Research Club officially recognized and to reach 100 subscribers on her video channel.

It's been modified in different ways, like putting an additional shotgun part under the muzzle so she could use ninjutsu bullets she made herself. Michiru says these are amalgams of her aspiration.

16010.Name: Hibiki (Cheer Squad)
16010.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Engineering Department who puts on a cheerleader outfit for game days.

Hibiki's sewing skills are sharp thanks to her love of cosplay, so she designs and makes special event outfits for all the members of the Engineering Department. She made this particular cheerleader outfit a long time ago, so it seems to be a bit small in some places.

16011.Name: Hasumi (Track)
16011.ProfileIntroduction:
Vice president of the Justice Task Force. She's wearing track clothes to participate in the Kivotos Halo Festival.

She joined the Executive Committee in place of Tsurugi, who's inexperienced with administrative work. Hasumi is trying to do her best and stay composed despite the president's excitement, but between troublemaking students and the smell of sweets coming from street vendors, distractions are everywhere.

Member of the Engineering Department at the Millennium Science School.

Socially inept and inarticulate compared to other students, but is a prolific inventor due to her innate talent for engineering. Her inventions are considered to be flawless masterpieces, but they often come equipped with baffling and obscure functions.

An agent of C&C, a secret organization from the Millennium Science School.

She's in charge of providing rear fire support under the call sign Zero-Two. Despite her intimidating appearance, she is the most cautious of C&C's agents and often ends up having to reel in Asuna and Akane when they get out of control during missions.

20002.Name: Saya

A genius inventor of the Shanhaijing Academy.

A prodigy who earned six degrees while still in primary school. However, she's known more for the way she causes trouble for others through her unruly antics than for her genius. She's always accompanied by her rat, Nezusuke, whom she's known since childhood and regards as family.

20003.Name: Mashiro
20003.CharacterSSRNew: Where do you need justice dispensed?
20003.ProfileIntroduction:
A devoted member of the Trinity General School's Justice Task Force.

Armed with a massive sniper rifle that towers over her, Mashiro stoically provides fire support.Though not much one for words, she isn't shy or socially inept and actually becomes quite talkative when it comes to justice.
20003.Hobby: Climbing to high places, keeping an observational diary

Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:HIT> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Manifestation of Justice
Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle that Mashiro uses to carry out her duties in the Justice Task Force.

Although it's a bit bulky to carry around, Mashiro claims it doesn't deter her faith in justice.

20004.Name: Mashiro (Swimsuit)
20004.CharacterSSRNew: Justice doesn't back down, even in sweltering heat!
20004.ProfileIntroduction:
A devoted Justice Task Force member who escorted Tsurugi to the beach.

Mashiro does not stop training while other students go out to play and make summer memories. She believes that this is the way of justice.

Weapon.Name: Manifestation of Justice
Weapon.Desc:
A sniper rifle that Mashiro uses to carry out her duties in the Justice Task Force.

Duty to justice continues even on the beach.

20005.Name: Hifumi (Swimsuit)
20005.CharacterSSRNew: Ahaha... It's a bit embarrassing having such a plain swimsuit.
20005.ProfileIntroduction:
A friendly Trinity Make-Up Work Club member visiting the beach with her friend.

She secretly borrowed a Crusader tank for a friend who had never been to the beach. Unfortunately, the Justice Task Force found out and she got in deep trouble. She happily rides the borrowed tank, just as clumsily as ever.
20005.Hobby: Collecting Peroro merch, shopping, listening to others

20007.ProfileIntroduction:
A virtual idol with a cheerful personality who loves to sing.

Originally, she only existed virtually online with no physical body, but she came to exist in the real world just in time for her live performance with the help of Kivotos' technology. She has quite a few hidden fans in Kivotos due to her ability to sing across time and space.

Skills.Desc: Summons Hatsune Miku to the selected location for 26s, restoring the HP of allies in a circular area by <?1> of Healing. While Miku is dancing, increases all nearby allies' <b:ATK> by <?2> as long as they stay within range.

Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:HealEffectiveness> by <?1>.

Weapon.Desc:
A gigantic t-shirt gun Miku uses to launch merchandise into the crowd at concerts.

There are diodes and other things embedded in the surface, and they sparkle beautifully with her music.

20008.Name: Ako
20008.CharacterSSRNew: There will be no mistakes as long as I'm here!
20008.ProfileIntroduction:
Senior administrator of the Gehenna Prefect Team and secretary to the head prefect, Hina.

Ako is always by Hina's side, assisting her. At first glance, she appears to be kind and good-natured, but she ruthlessly suppresses rule-breakers, showing no mercy. The students of Gehenna often call her "Hina's pet," but she doesn't seem to mind.

Skills.Desc: Increases the <b:CriticalChance> by <?1> and <b:CriticalDamage> by <?2> of one ally for 16s.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Beginning Tactical Support
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Hot Shot
Weapon.Desc:
A pistol used by Ako.

This pistol was awarded to Ako for reaching the position of senior administrator with painstaking effort. She always carries it with her and takes very good care of it.

20009.Name: Cherino (Hot Spring)
20009.CharacterSSRNew: Kneel before the magnificence of Purginator No. 1!
20009.ProfileIntroduction:
The president of the Red Winter Federal Academy who came to Hot Springs Resort No. 227 to enjoy a vacation.

At first, she was planning to demolish the resort that Spec Ops built without her permission, but satisfied with the hospitality of Nodoka and the Spec Ops students, she's decided to extend her stay indefinitely. Doesn't really enjoy getting into the hot springs despite how much she likes resting at the resort and eatings its food options.
20009.Hobby: Doling out demerits, purging, snowball fights

Skills.Name: Purginator No. 1, Mobilize!
Skills.Desc: Deploys Cherino riding Purginator No. 1 for 50s, with an additional <?1> of Cherino's <b:ATK>. Every 3 normal attacks, Purginator No. 1 activates the skill "Total Annihilation!", firing a shot that deals <?2> damage to one enemy plus <?3> damage to the target and enemies in a fan-shaped area behind them. Only one tactical support vehicle may be deployed at any given time.

Skills.Desc: Every 15s, deals <?1> damage to enemies in a circular area.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Power of the 'Stache!
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:CriticalDamage> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Chistka
Weapon.Desc:
A pistol Cherino uses to purge dissenters.

Tomoe modified some of its materials to prevent it from rusting, even in high temperature and humidity.

Gear.Name: Comrade Bathtime
Gear.Desc:
A souvenir from Red Winter Academy, carefully handmade by gluing a mustache onto a mass-produced rubber duck.
Cherino claims that they're childish toys which she has no interest in, but rumor has it one has been seen in the bathtub after she's finished...

20010.Name: Nodoka (Hot Spring)
20010.CharacterSSRNew: I will serve my guests with all my heart!
20010.ProfileIntroduction:
The owner of Hot Springs Resort No. 227 who runs the large resort with the Spec Ops students.

She is still suspended from the Red Winter Office, but finds herself with newfound wealth when a hot spring suddenly erupts at the Former Institute. However, her troubles continue as students with strong personalities from the Red Winter Federal Academy come to disrupt her business for various reasons.

Skills.Name: Hot Springs Resort No. 227, Open for Business!
Skills.Desc: Summons Nodoka to the selected location for 32s. Every 3s, Nodoka throws one of three snacks that restore HP by different amounts of Healing, to the ally with the lowest HP in range. Hot Spring Manju: of Healing. Corn Stick: of Healing. Milk: of Healing.

Skills.Name: The Hostess' Welcome
Skills.Desc: Every 25s, increases the <b:HealEffectiveness> of the ally with the lowest HP by <?1>.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1>.

Skills.Name: Hot Springs Therapy+
Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Hot Springs Heat
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Sagittarius Night
Weapon.Desc:
A submachine gun Nodoka carries everywhere.

It is usually used to guide others around the dark paths of the hot springs resort at night, but it is also needed to "serve" rude customers.

20011.Name: Serika (New Year)
20011.CharacterSSRNew: Well, if it's for Sensei, I'll lift up a prayer or two.
20011.ProfileIntroduction:
The smart treasurer of the Abydos Foreclosure Task Force.

A diligent girl who works several part-time jobs to help the Foreclosure Task Force, she is now working as a miko for the new year. Serika is giving it her patented best after being told she would get higher pay if she plays a convincing miko.

Skills.Name: Part-Time Interference!
Skills.Desc: Deals <?1> damage to enemies in an arc-shaped area and decreases their <d:CriticalDamage> by <?2> for 30s.

Skills.Name: A Miko Cheers for Everyone!
Skills.Desc: Every 40s, increases the <b:ATK> of all allies in a circular area by <?1> for 30s.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Full-Time Tenacity
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:CriticalDamageRateResist> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Sincerity
Weapon.Desc:
An assault rifle Serika carries with her whenever she goes to work part time.

She also takes it to her part-time miko job and uses it to quiet troublemakers who cause a ruckus at the New Year's event.

20012.Name: Sena
20012.CharacterSSRNew: Where is the corpse...? I mean, where is the injured patient?
20012.ProfileIntroduction:
President of Gehenna's always busy Medical Emergency Club.

She transports the wounded with a stoic face no matter the situation. She may seem apathetic as she treats the wounded like inanimate cargo, but she has never once complained about transporting numerous injured people all over Gehenna.

Tactical Ambulance 11 increases the <b:ATK> of allies in a circular area around it by <?2> and continuously restores their HP by <?3> of Healing every 10s as long as they stay within range. Only one tactical support vehicle may be deployed at any given time.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Weapon.Desc:
Sena's sawed-off grenade launcher.

Used to quickly clear obstacles during emergency dispatches. Also used to occasionally clear people who are in the way.

20013.Name: Chihiro
20013.ProfileIntroduction:
Vice president of Veritas, Millennium Science School's hacker group.

A genius programmer with excellent hacking skills, she is not afraid of getting her hands dirty when the task demands, whether it's going undercover or in the field. She actually has common sense unlike most of Veritas' devilish members. She is always emphasizing proper hacking ethics to other members.

Skills.Desc: Deals damage to one enemy. If the target is Heavy armor type, inflicts for .

Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:OppressionPower> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: Backdoor
Weapon.Desc:
An automatic rifle used by Chihiro.

According to Chihiro, it's the fastest way to find out an encrypted password.

20014.Name: Saki
20014.CharacterSSRNew: Call sign, RABBIT 2. Sensitivity is good.
20014.ProfileIntroduction:
The point woman of the SRT Academy RABBIT Squad. Call sign is "RABBIT 2."

Saki enrolled in the SRT Academy to live the life of discipline she'd always dreamed of. When the academy closed down, she, along with her squad, refused to give up on their school and began camping out in the park in protest. A star student, she still carries around her textbooks and SRT manuals to this day. She enjoys foraging for wild greens and trash that can be repurposed as supplies.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:ATK> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: Point Woman's Lead
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Weapon.Name: RABBIT Type 26 Machine Gun
Weapon.Desc:
A standard machine gun Saki received from the SRT Academy.
It's hard to maintain, but it guarantees great firepower as long as it's serviced well.

20015.Name: Kaede
20015.CharacterSSRNew: As usual, I'm gonna work hard to become a proper lady!
20015.ProfileIntroduction:
An enthusiastic member of the Hyakkiyako Academy Inner Discipline Club.

She used to be infamous for spreading mischief around town, but after meeting Tsubaki and Mimori by chance, she was inspired to be a proper lady like them and joined the Inner Discipline Club. Kaede never skips her training to be a proper lady, but still always seems to cause trouble.
20015.Hobby: Playing pranks (but is trying to be good lately), catching beetles

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1>.

Skills.Desc: Increases <b:HealPower> by <?1> plus a further <?2>.

Skills.Name: I Can Try Harder!
Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:MAXHP> by <?1>.

Weapon.Desc:
A signal pistol Kaede always carries around.
Literally, it's a gun used to signal when something is found. Kaede mainly uses it when she comes across a bad student or a rare Mushiqueen card.

20016.Name: Iroha
20016.CharacterSSRNew: Do you need me? Oh, well. All right, then.
20016.ProfileIntroduction:
"A member of the Pandemonium Society.

There's nothing Iroha hates more than being bothered. She spends much of her time trying to figure out how to escape company. She even constantly carries a book around so people will leave her alone, but the Pandemonium Society (Makoto, to be exact) always interrupts her anyway. She begrudgingly serves as an executive of the Pandemonium Society, only finding comfort in their mascot, Ibuki."

Skills.Desc: Deploys Iroha riding Toramaru for 55s, with an additional <?1> of Iroha's <b:ATK>. Every 15s, Toramaru activates the skill "Aim & Fire Main Armament", firing a shell that deals <?2> damage to one enemy and splits, dealing the same damage to up to 2 nearby enemies (up to 2 times). Only one tactical support vehicle may be deployed at any given time.

Skills.Desc: Increases all allies' <b:ATK> by <?1>.

Weapon.Desc:
A pistol Iroha carries around.
Since Iroha is the tank commander of the Pandemonium Society, she always complains that it's cumbersome to carry around something she never uses. But she still maintains it perfectly, which is typical Iroha-behavior.

20017.Name: Hiyori
20017.CharacterSSRNew: Oh, I got lucky today. Heehee...
20017.ProfileIntroduction:
An Arius Squad member that gives a gloomy impression.

Hiyori follows other Arius students around, always crying about her latest heavy burden. She has low self-esteem and a negative personality. She tends to be pessimistic about everything in the world, and believes the only purpose of life is suffering.

Skills.Name: T-Take This!

20018.Name: Moe
20018.CharacterSSRNew: This is RABBIT 3. Where's the next bombing site?
20018.ProfileIntroduction:
The operator of the SRT Academy RABBIT Squad. Call sign is RABBIT 3. 
She entered the SRT Academy because she admired their massive firepower, but the academy was suddenly closed. She's currently living in a park with her platoon members. She's bizarre in that she enjoys blowing up and destroying things, but her ability as an operator is quite impressive. She's addicted to sugar and always has a lollipop in her mouth.

Weapon.Desc: The standard pistol Moe was given at the SRT Academy. Despite being a pistol, it has a rapid rate of fire and can empty a magazine in an instant.

20019.Name: Akane (Bunny)
20019.CharacterSSRNew: My Master's maid... Well, I guess I'm your rabbit now.
20019.ProfileIntroduction:
A C&C agent wearing a Bunny Girl costume as her disguise.

Even in unfamiliar environments, Akane keeps the team together, always in perfect uniform, and blazes their way forward with large amounts of C4. But she seems preoccupied lately... Maybe she's too excited about her new bunny outfit?

Weapon.Desc:
This pistol is Akane's constant companion.

It's been customized to be perfect for infiltration missions.

20020.Name: Himari
20020.CharacterSSRNew: Haha! Is it finally time to shine for Millennium's super genius hacker?
20020.ProfileIntroduction:
The former president of Veritas, a hacker club at the Millennium School, and the current president of the Super Phenomenon Task Force.

She styles herself as a super genius hacker, and claims she has a degree in Omniscience, which only three people have received in Millennium's history. However, no one's ever been able to confirm the existence of such a degree. Himari relishes this, believing that secrets make a girl more beautiful. None can deny that she is an extremely talented hacker with a strange taste for the occult.

Weapon.Desc:
Himari's pistol.

A gun with a simple and elegant exterior. Himari uses it sparingly. "A flower blooming on a rocky clifftop is an extraordinary sight. Just like that flower, I'm in bloom." - Himari

20021.Name: Hanae (Christmas)
20021.CharacterSSRNew: Merry Christmas! Were you expecting Santa Claus? Your guardian angel is here instead!
20021.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Trinity Remedial Knights. She's wearing a Santa costume to celebrate Christmas.

Because she has a very active personality, Hanae needs a Santa costume that allows her freedom of movement. For a girl who finds everything exciting, Christmas is nothing less than a month-long festival. She carries bundles of presents everywhere she goes, and rings a bell to fill everyone with the spirit of the season.

Weapon.Desc:
Hanae's assault rifle.

Even on Christmas, a time of peace, her gun spreads joy.

20022.Name: Fuuka (New Year)
20022.CharacterSSRNew: Did you have any New Year's Eve noodles? I hope everything goes well for us this year!
20022.ProfileIntroduction:
Fuuka is dressed up in a kimono for the New Year.

She is hoping for peaceful days in the upcoming year, but given her surroundings, that doesn't seem likely.
20022.Hobby: Making home-cooked meals, packing bento lunches

Fuuka's submachine gun.

Her wish for the New Year is that she won't have to use it, but the world doesn't always grant her wishes...

20023.Name: Kanna
20023.CharacterSSRNew: I will serve the citizens faithfully.
20023.ProfileIntroduction:
A police student in charge of the Public Peace Bureau at the Valkyrie Police School.

She's better known by the nickname "Feral Hound," because she never gives up on a crime once it's in her sights. She'll investigate tenaciously until she uncovers the truth. People see her as hot-tempered because of her unusual, ferocious looks and her nickname, but in reality she's calm and down-to-earth.
20023.Hobby: Reading detective stories, watching detective movies

Despite its rugged design, it's light and easy to operate. Kanna prefers it, since she spends more time on paperwork than fieldwork.

20024.Name: Nagisa
20024.CharacterSSRNew: And how are you? Greetings from Trinity.
20024.ProfileIntroduction:
The leader of Filius, one of the allied factions that makes up Trinity General School, and the host of the Tea Party.

Although she has a sweet and friendly demeanor, she rarely reveals her true feelings, so she's not very approachable. Her hobby is preparing tea and refreshments for tea parties. Many Trinity students long to attend her get-togethers.
20024.Hobby: Collecting tea leaves, baking pastries, gardening

23000.ProfileIntroduction:
A cheerful member of the Trinity After-School Sweets Club.

Has a relaxed and easy-going personality and cherishes the time she spends sampling desserts and chatting with her friends. Her favorite dessert is ice cream, and she's recently gotten hooked on mint chocolate chip.
23000.Hobby: Checking out dessert shops, tea parties.

Airi's SMG.

The name is taken from one of the desserts at a shop she frequents.

23001.Name: Fuuka
23001.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the School Lunch Club that manages the Gehenna Academy's dining hall.

A kind and earnest student, making her a bit of a rarity at Gehenna. She prepares and serves hundreds of meals every morning for the students of Gehenna. She's a good cook, but her skills are written off due to the dining hall's lack of manpower. Still, she refuses to give up and is constantly looking for ways to improve the menu.
23001.Hobby: Cooking homestyle dishes, packing bento lunches

Weapon.Desc:
A submachine gun Fuuka carries everywhere.

It was originally intended to control the occasional troublemakers in the dining hall, but those troublemakers usually quiet down before Fuuka gets to use it.

23002.Name: Hanae
23002.ProfileIntroduction:
A cheerful and energetic first-year member of the Trinity Remedial Knights.

Hanae has a vivacious personality and a positive outlook on life, but when she sees a patient, she can get too worked up and often actually worsens their condition. She's a bit odd at times, but patients under her care seem to recover more quickly regardless of their affliction.

Weapon.Name: Happy Smile Gun
Weapon.Desc:
An assault rifle that Hanae uses when examining patients.

This rifle brings a happy smile to any patient that sees it.

23003.Name: Hare
23003.ProfileIntroduction:
An engineer of Veritas, the hacker group of the Millennium Science School.

An unprecedented genius even amongst the brilliant minds at Millennium. Most of the school's cutting-edge technology was developed by her. Even with all these achievements, she remains humble, friendly, and considerate towards her peers.

Weapon.Desc:

Gear.Name: Athena-3
Gear.Desc: A spherical drone that always follows Hare around. Named after the goddess of wisdom, it's equipped with artificial intelligence that can experience and learn on its own, but it often works against the intentions of Hare in unexpected ways.

23004.Name: Utaha
23004.ProfileIntroduction:
President of the Engineering Department at the Millennium Science School.

Has invented a variety of robots, if only to stake her claim to the title of president of the Engineering Department. Her pet robot Thundergun has been determined to possess combat capabilities equivalent to a hundred PMC combat automata.

A submachine gun with a simple design that Utaha modified herself.

Gear.Desc:
A set of tools in a custom toolbox, assembled and organized to Utaha's preferences.
It's very likely that this set, made and maintained with a meister's pride, has no equal in all of Kivotos.

23005.Name: Ayane
23005.ProfileIntroduction:
The diligent secretary of the Abydos Foreclosure Task Force.

A hard-working stickler for rules and regulations, she does her best to contribute to the revitalization of Abydos High School.

You will hardly ever see this pistol as long as you speak and act with common sense in front of Ayane.

23006.ProfileIntroduction:
President of the Festival Operations Department at Hyakkiyako Academy.

The mascot of Momoyodou, the Hyakkiyako's traditional tea house. Acts clumsy, but only because it sells her image as an idol. In truth, she's an expert flirt willing to do anything for the success of the festivals and Momoyodou. Wears her heart on her sleeve, making her an easy read for her friends as well as Sensei.
23006.Hobby: Serving and charming customers, Idol Punch

23007.ProfileIntroduction:
A friendly girl from the Make-Up Work Club.

She may appear like a quiet and elegant young lady at first, but a bevy of inappropriate and lewd comments spew out any time Hanako opens her mouth. Every member of the Make-Up Work Club gets nervous whenever Hanako starts speaking.

23008.ProfileIntroduction:
A sincere and benevolent girl affiliated with the Sisterhood.

She always greets Trinity students with a friendly smile. Despite her cuteness, many come to her for counseling because of the calm and relaxing air about her. She is self-critical and always considers herself as lacking, but she dreams of becoming a great Sister like her upperclassmen.

26000.ProfileIntroduction:
She is in charge of medical aid at Gehenna Academy's Prefect Team.

Chinatsu is one of the few people with common sense among the obsessively dogmatic Prefect Team. She's usually the one who prevents other members like Ako and Iori from running amok. Her tone can be harsh and give the impression of being just as cold as any other member of the Prefect Team, but she is actually a sweet young girl who melts at the sight of cute animals.

26001.Name: Kotama
26001.ProfileIntroduction:
A hacker of Veritas, Millennium Science School's infamous hacking group.

Wiretapping is her specialty, and she takes great pleasure in eavesdropping on other people's private conversations. A socially awkward young lady who addresses even younger students with formal deference. In real life, she's mousy and shy, but on the internet she's a surprisingly glib wordsmith.

26002.Name: Juri
26002.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the School Lunch Club that manages the Gehenna Academy's dining hall.

Like Fuuka, she's a hard worker who pours her heart and soul into cooking meals for the other students. However, her cooking is so bad that it's grotesque, so her efforts are ultimately useless. But she continues to strive to hopefully improve her cooking under Fuuka's encouragement and guidance.

but for some reason, Juri uses it as a cooking tool.

26003.Name: Serina
26003.ProfileIntroduction:
A kind-hearted girl affiliated with the Trinity Remedial Knights.

A virtuous person who enjoys charity work, her concern for the health of those around her has earned her a reputation as a sort of mother hen. Despite having a somewhat timid personality and avoiding quarrels and conflict, she is always ready to stand up against enemies who threaten the peace.

26004.Name: Shimiko
26004.ProfileIntroduction:
Librarian of the Trinity Library Committee.

A bookworm and a bibliophile, she is one of the few students who has read every single tome in Trinity Library. She loves recommending books as much as she does reading them, and has a habit of making book recommendations to people she's just met based on their preferences.

26005.ProfileIntroduction:
A member of the Trinity After-School Sweets Club.

A girl with a height complex that gives off the impression of a small, angry animal. Constantly fixated on appearing more mature, her tendency to wear her heart on her sleeve gets her into trouble. She can't help but smile widely when visiting dessert cafes to sample the latest limited-edition treats.

26006.ProfileIntroduction:
A student suspended from Red Winter Academy and on probation in Former Institute 227.

She was suspended for constantly monitoring Sensei through a telescope. Nodoka wants to observe the world's beauty and sees Sensei in the same vein. Being in Spec Ops No. 227 has taught her to be careful with what little money she has to get by.

A flashlight is attached to illuminate the road on dark nights.

26007.Name: Ayane (Swimsuit)
26007.ProfileIntroduction:
The secretary of the Abydos Foreclosure Task Force who flew the group to the beach for summer vacation. 
She wants to forget about her arduous daily grind and have a pleasant vacation, but she can never hide her strong work ethic, even while relaxing.

26008.ProfileIntroduction: President of the Festival Department, full of ambition and aspirations for the summer. The president's passion is to spread Momoyodou franchises all over Kivotos.
